es.ull.iis.util
Class RoundedPeriodicCycle

java.lang.Object
  es.ull.iis.util.Cycle
      es.ull.iis.util.PeriodicCycle
          es.ull.iis.util.RoundedPeriodicCycle

public class RoundedPeriodicCycle
extends PeriodicCycle

An special periodic cycle which rounds (or trunks) the incidence of events. It uses three attributes

  • type can be ROUND, CEIL or FLOOR, depending on if you need to round, get the ceil or the floor of the value;
  • factor indicates the value to adjust the result: what you're going to get are multiples of the factor;
  • shift sets a displacement to be added to the result.
The key point of this cycle is that it preserves the behavior of the underlying period, but it rounds the events. For example, suppose that you have a periodic cycle which generates events in 1, 4, 10, 11, 14... The result of a rounded periodic cycle with factor 5.0, shift 1.0 and type ROUND would be 1, 6, 11, 16, 16.

Author:
Iván Castilla Rodríguez
